pgTitle: List of tornadoes in the April 25–28, 2011 tornado outbreak (Part 2)

headers.text: List of reported tornadoes – Wednesday, April 27, 2011

List of reported tornadoes – Wednesday, April 27, 2011

List of reported tornadoes – Wednesday, April 27, 2011
List of reported tornadoes – Wednesday, April 27, 2011

rows.text: A feet (m) high communication tower was bent to the ground, three homes were destroyed, and many others were damaged.
Nearly 100 homes were damaged and trees were downed.
Several homes were badly damaged, a trailer was flipped and destroyed, and trees and power lines were downed.
An old building was destroyed, with a collapsed wall and a caved-in roof. Many trees were downed as well.
A couple of homes and a tractor shed suffered minor damage.

A mobile home was destroyed and several others were damaged, a store in a structure like a mobile home was destroyed, several homes sustained major roof damage, numerous outbuildings and barns damaged or destroyed, numerous trees were blown down, and 15 power poles were snapped. Three people were injured.
Numerous trees were snapped and several houses suffered shingle damage. A mobile home and a building both lost part of their roofs.
Many trees were downed, several of which landed on homes.
A barn suffered roof damage and trees and power lines were downed.
Hundreds of trees and three wooden high-tension poles were snapped.
One home was pushed off its blocks, a mobile home and shed were destroyed, one home lost part of its roof, a tin roof was lifted off a church camp, and hundreds of trees and power poles were downed.
A storage shelter was damaged and trees were downed.
Trees and power poles were snapped.
A storage room was destroyed, three homes suffered roof damage, and several trees were downed.
Thousands of trees were downed, several of which fell onto homes, barns, and sheds.
A barn was destroyed and a few trees were downed.
A few homes and barns were damaged and thousands of trees were downed, many of which fell on numerous structures.
A shed had roof damage and a tree fell onto a house.
1 death– Significant damage to homes, mobile homes, and a gas station. Thousands of trees and power poles were downed.
Trees were downed, one of which landed on a house and caused severe roof damage. Two outbuildings were destroyed as well.
Farm buildings and a home were damaged and trees were downed.
A number of homes, businesses, and apartments were damaged, and a large metal storage building was destroyed.
A number of homes and mobile homes were either damaged or destroyed along the path of this tornado. Numerous trees and power lines were downed as well. Eight people were injured.
Homes suffered minor damage and trees were downed.
Several homes and mobile homes were either damaged or destroyed and many trees were downed. Two people were injured.
Trees were downed and agricultural crops, silos, grain bins, sheds, farm buildings, a radio tower, and irrigation pivots were damaged.
Numerous homes and mobile homes were either damaged or destroyed. Damage occurred to other structures as well and numerous trees were downed.
A house and a mobile home were damaged and many trees were downed.
Tornado lifted a concrete bridge and severely damaged many homes.
Numerous trees were downed, some of which landed on homes. Three homes sustained roof, window, and garage damage and one building sustained awning damage. Three docks were also damaged.
Several homes and outbuildings were damaged and thousands of trees were downed.
Businesses and homes in downtown Berry had roof and wall damage. Mobile homes were destroyed as well.

Multiple homes damaged or destroyed, one of which only had a foundation left. Three mobile homes were destroyed as well. Brick buildings were badly damaged in the downtown area of Cordova and many trees were downed. This area was hit by an EF4 tornado that afternoon.
Numerous trees fell on power lines, cars, homes, etc.
Many homes were heavily damaged by fallen trees. 20 people were injured.
Outbuildings and barns were destroyed and several chicken houses had roof damage.
The tornado caused significant damage to two homes, shifted a garage shifted off of its foundation, and downed a few trees. Five people were injured.
Trees were snapped and uprooted. A mobile home rolled several times and hit a tree. Many chicken houses were either damaged or destroyed.
Large trees were snapped and uprooted. Several chicken houses suffered substantial roof damage.
Damage to a church and some homes.
Several barns were destroyed. Homes were damaged by fallen trees. Damage to power poles and outbuildings.
Trees were downed along the path. Some houses and chicken houses were damaged.
A trailer, piers, and sheds were destroyed. Several homes had roof damage and RV campers were also damaged. Tornado closely followed Lake Guntersville for most of its duration.
Large trees were uprooted and one house sustained significant roof loss.
Damage mostly to trees with roof damage to one home.
1 death - Numerous trees snapped and uprooted and a mobile home destroyed. Tornado took very similar path to a violent EF4 tornado that occurred later in the day that also began near Section.
Trees were snapped and uprooted. Three barns were destroyed and a home was partially collapsed.
Numerous trees were snapped and a house lost its roof.
Minor roof and gutter damage to some homes.
Damage to several industrial buildings at Decatur Industrial Park. Passed over Pryor Field causing it to lose power shortly before lifting.
Trees and signage damage near Tanner High School.
Roofs were damaged and trees and power lines were downed.
Damage mostly to trees with minor shingle and gutter damage to some homes.
Roofs were damaged and trees were downed.
Damage to numerous homes, mostly to the roofs. Numerous trees damaged and fences downed. An RV was overturned as well.
Several homes suffered minor roof damage and multiple trees were downed.

Many site-built houses and mobile homes were badly damaged, with others being completely destroyed. Many trees were snapped and outbuildings were destroyed. The Winston Furniture Company and Fontaine Trailer Company in Haleyville suffered extensive damage as well. 25 people were injured.
Two homes and several barns and outbuildings were destroyed. Hundreds of trees were downed as well.
One house sustained minor damage and trees were snapped.
Many trees were downed, a few of which fell on homes.
A house and two barns were damaged, an outbuilding was destroyed, and many trees were downed.
A large metal farm building was flattened and two small barns were collapsed. Four power poles were snapped and many trees were knocked down, some of which landed on houses.
One home had major roof damage and numerous trees were downed.
An outbuilding sustained minor roof damage and many trees were downed.
A carport and the roof of a mobile home were damaged and multiple trees were downed.
A mobile home park sustained significant damage including two mobile homes blown off their foundation with others damaged. Damage to homes and churches along with trees and telephone poles snapped.
Many trees were snapped and uprooted and several homes sustained roof damage.
yards (m) wide tornado snapped hundreds of trees and damaged several homes and structures. One person was injured.
In the Country Park subdivision of Murfreesboro, the tornado uprooted several trees and snapped off others.
Hundreds of trees were snapped. Several mobile homes and a church were damaged.
Hundreds of trees snapped and uprooted. Some homes suffered roof damage.
Brief tornado with minor damage. Maximum path width was yards (m).
Thousands of trees snapped and uprooted.
Numerous trees downed, some of which landed on homes and cars.
Very brief tornado, damage was limited to trees and minor property damage.
1 death - Many trees were snapped. Numerous homes and businesses were damaged by the tornado.
A few homes and businesses were damaged and several trees were downed.
Numerous trees and power lines were downed. A few structures were damaged as well.
Numerous trees were downed along with power lines. Some buildings received damage as well.
Three mobile homes were destroyed and other structures were damaged. One person was injured.
Minor to moderate roof damage to several homes. Trees were downed as well.
1 death–Many trees were downed and a few structures were damaged. Mobile homes were destroyed as well.
Mostly tree damage along the path.
Minor to moderate roof damage to several homes and numerous trees downed.
A number of homes were damaged and a hardware store was destroyed. Two people suffered minor injuries.
A few trees and powerlines were downed.
Many trees and power lines were downed.
Numerous trees were downed and several homes suffered roof damage.
3 deaths– Many trees downed and several structures were either damaged or destroyed.
yards (m) wide tornado downed several trees.
The top of a two-story building was blown off and several other structures were damaged. Numerous trees were downed as well. One person was injured.
Minor roof damage to a few homes along with trees downed.
Numerous trees were downed along the path.
Minor roof damage to a few homes along with trees downed.
Several homes were damaged and numerous trees and powerlines were downed. One person was injured.
yards (m) wide tornado downed a few trees.
Several homes were damaged, with one being destroyed. Many trees were downed. Five people were injured.
Numerous trees downed and a hospital was damaged.
Tornado moved across Chilhowee Lake and downed several trees in the Cades Cove area.
Many trees and powerlines were downed. The roof was removed from a building and other buildings were damaged.
Several trees downed and one outbuilding destroyed.
A few trees were downed. The tornado was forced to lift because of steep terrain but touched back down later as the Camp Creek tornado.
Several trees were downed in the park.
2 deaths - Homes and buildings destroyed along with numerous trees snapped.

2 deaths– High-end EF3 caused major devastation to South Central, Horse Creek, and Cassi Creek Communities. Numerous homes were damaged or destroyed and extensive tree damage was noted. Vehicles were tossed and multiple barns were destroyed with sheet metal roofing wrapped around trees. Tornado paralleled and crossed the path of the Camp Creek tornado from a few hours earlier.
Touched down in downtown Greensburg, where windows and chimneys were damaged. Worst damage was in town's industrial park. Northeast of town, a mobile home was damaged and two barns were destroyed.
Barns and outbuildings destroyed. Several homes had minor damage, mostly from falling trees.
Fives homes were damaged, one severely. Thousands of trees were snapped and uprooted and two trailers were thrown 20 feet.
15 homes were destroyed with 50 others damaged. A log cabin was completely flattened and thousands of trees and power lines were snapped.
2 deaths - Numerous houses were damaged or destroyed, some completely flattened. Numerous trees were snapped and uprooted.

Tornado uprooted trees and destroyed metal storage buildings. Aluminum siding was torn off of a building and a garden center was damaged. Homes received garage door and shingle damage as well. A slide at a local pool was torn from its bracings and a fence was downed.
Minor damage to local buildings and many trees were down.
Roof damage to business office building, two storage garage doors blown in, blown out windows, and partially downed chain link fence.
Tornado lifted carport awning and other light debris at the Bay Airport.
Roof damage to five homes and one business garage. Tree limbs were snapped and a storage shed was destroyed.
Damaged farm irrigation equipment, two telephone poles down, a few broken tree limbs.
Tornado touched down over open fields with two trees being uprooted.
Brief tornado spotted with no significant damage.
Tornado spotted lofting debris in a wooded area.
Several homes sustained roof damage and multiple trees were snapped and downed.
Tornado was caught on video by a storm chaser. Numerous trees snapped and uprooted.

1 death– Tornado touched down seven miles Northwest of Halifax and traveled northeast, damaging or destroying 20 to 30 homes. Outbuildings were destroyed and numerous trees were snapped and uprooted. Eight people were injured.
Very narrow tornado downed numerous trees.
Tornado touched down in the village community of New Bristow damaging a shopping plaza, garage doors, and horse sheds. Homes sustained siding and shingle damage. Many signs and trees were downed.
Damage mostly to fallen trees with some damaging homes.
At least 200 trees uprooted or snapped at a campground, with damage to a bath house.
Several trees downed in a heavily wooded area.
Trees were downed and a few homes sustained siding and shingle damage.
A barn was heavily damaged and numerous trees were snapped and uprooted. Two homes were damaged and a large camper was blown over.
Large trees were snapped and several structures were damaged.
One camper and several trucks were hit by fallen trees.
Brief, intermittent tornado caused tree damage and flipped a mobile home.
